id: pm-og1v
title: "Relative lancedb vector-store path resolves against process cwd, creating nested .agents/pm/.agents/pm stores"
description: "Settings store a workspace-relative lancedb path (default .agents/pm/search/lancedb/). getLanceDbSnapshotPath/resolveLanceDbStore resolved it with path.resolve() against process cwd, so any pm invocation from a workspace subdirectory (including detached background-refresh children that inherit the parent cwd) silently created a second vector store under that subdirectory. Observed artifact: .agents/pm/.agents/pm/search/lancedb/.pm-cli-local-vectors/pm_items.json created 2026-07-06T08:22:48Z (matches vectorization-status.json generated_at), i.e. a refresh ran with cwd=<repo>/.agents/pm."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: "area:search",bug,paths,vector-store
created_at: "2026-07-06T08:44:42.249Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T09:52:59.549Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "pm search/reindex/health run from a workspace subdirectory never create .agents/pm/.agents/**; regression tests cover conventional root, bare --path root, absolute path, and no-root back-compat"
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: "Relative LanceDB paths now resolve against the pmRoot-derived workspace root across search, health, reindex, and mutation semantic refresh."
expected_result: "pm search/reindex/health from workspace subdirectories do not create .agents/pm/.agents vector stores; regression tests cover conventional root, bare root, absolute path, and back-compat."
actual_result: "Focused linked tests passed, temp-dir subdirectory smoke proved the anchored path and absence of nested .agents/pm/.agents, and full coverage passed 100/100/100/100."
